Sentencas: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) is a promising cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells due to its high oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) activity.
Titulo: Interface engineering of yttrium stabilized zirconia/gadolinium doped ceria bi-layer electrolyte solid oxide fuel cell for boosting electrochemical performance

Sentencas: A gadolinium-doped ceria (GDC) barrier layer is essential to preventing side reactions between LSCF and an yttrium-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte.
Titulo: Interface engineering of yttrium stabilized zirconia/gadolinium doped ceria bi-layer electrolyte solid oxide fuel cell for boosting electrochemical performance

Sentencas: However, several challenges are associated with the coating of GDC barrier layer on the YSZ electrolyte, including delamination of the GDC layer due to sinterability differences and formation of an insulating layer at a high annealing temperature.
Titulo: Interface engineering of yttrium stabilized zirconia/gadolinium doped ceria bi-layer electrolyte solid oxide fuel cell for boosting electrochemical performance

Sentencas: In this study, we describe a structure for a newly designed interfacial layer consisting of a GDC barrier layer and a nano-web structured LSCF thin-film layer (NW-LSCF) through a facile spin-coating method.
Titulo: Interface engineering of yttrium stabilized zirconia/gadolinium doped ceria bi-layer electrolyte solid oxide fuel cell for boosting electrochemical performance

Sentencas: A dense GDC barrier layer with a thickness of approximately 400 nm was successfully applied to the surface of a YSZ electrolyte without delamination at a low annealing temperature.
Titulo: Interface engineering of yttrium stabilized zirconia/gadolinium doped ceria bi-layer electrolyte solid oxide fuel cell for boosting electrochemical performance

Sentencas: The high surface area of the NW-LSCF enhanced ORR due to an increased triple-phase boundary length.
Titulo: Interface engineering of yttrium stabilized zirconia/gadolinium doped ceria bi-layer electrolyte solid oxide fuel cell for boosting electrochemical performance

Sentencas: Cells employing a GDC barrier layer and NW-LSCF interlayer exhibited improved electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Interface engineering of yttrium stabilized zirconia/gadolinium doped ceria bi-layer electrolyte solid oxide fuel cell for boosting electrochemical performance

Sentencas: Peak power density reached 1.29 W/cm(2) at an operating temperature of 550 degrees C and 2.14 W/cm(2) at 650 degrees C.
Titulo: Interface engineering of yttrium stabilized zirconia/gadolinium doped ceria bi-layer electrolyte solid oxide fuel cell for boosting electrochemical performance
